io.sarl.sre.services.probing.probes

Class BigIntegerFieldProbe

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.sarl.sre.services.probing.probes.AbstractProbe<T>
      • io.sarl.sre.services.probing.probes.AbstractFieldProbe<BigInteger>
        • io.sarl.sre.services.probing.probes.BigIntegerFieldProbe
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Probe<BigInteger>

    public class BigIntegerFieldProbe
extends AbstractFieldProbe<BigInteger>
    Probe implementation is linked to a primitive big integer field, or a field that could be assimilated to a big integer primitive. A probe is thread-safe. This probe make a buffer of the values. In order to be updated, the Probe.sync() function must be invoked. Then, the new value is read from the associated field, and the probe listeners are notified.
